To run this server, type `npm install`
Then type `npm run prod`

Open one browser to `http://localhost:8000/`

Open another browser tab to `http://localhost:8000/receiver.html`

Update the values in `http://localhost:8000/` and watch them change in `http://localhost:8000/receiver.html`

The data being sent to `http://localhost:8000/receiver.html`will look like this:

```js
{
  "title": "This is the title for this block.",
  "image": "https://cdn.masto.host/podcastindexsocial/accounts/avatars/000/015/466/original/1dcbcde7619f90a7.png",
  "line": [
    "this is line 1",
    "this is line 2",
    "this is line 3",
    "this is line 4"
  ],
  "link": {
    "text": "This is the text for the link",
    "url": "https://podcastindex.social"
  },
  "description": "this would be an area for something like show notes",
  "value": {
    "type": "lightning",
    "method": "keysend",
    "destinations": {
      "name": "The Split Kit",
      "address": "030a58b8653d32b99200a2334cfe913e51dc7d155aa0116c176657a4f1722677a3",
      "customKey": "696969",
      "customValue": "boPNspwDdt7axih5DfKs",
      "split": "5",
      "fee": "false"
    }
  },
  "type": "person"
}
```
